The paper deals with lower bounds for a fundamental problem in text processing, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computer science. The problem involves preprocessing a long string into a data structure to quickly identify substrings within a certain distance from a query string. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
